
0.8.0 2010-07-xx Andrew Wedgbury <wedge@sconemad.com>

        * Major SconeScript improvements:
         - Short circuit | and & operators.
	 - Combination assignment operators e.g. +=.
         - map (associative array) type.
	 - Authority levels allowing arg call security.
         - Lots of bug fixes.
         - Scripted test system.
	 - JSON compatible literal initialiser synax.
	 - New object serialiser.
         - Regular Expression support (RegExp) using PCRE.

	* Combined I/O multiplexer and job scheduling system:
         - Low CPU overhead
	 - Flexible thread pool system.
	 - Job scheduling system for running background tasks.

        * HTTP module improvements:
         - Reliable multi-threading support.
         - HTTP Authentication realm support using htpasswd files.
         - Session management.
         - Multipart POST processing.

        * New module: 'sconesite' web site management, includes:
          - XML template driven page generation.
          - Server side inline SconeScript.
          - Supports multipart form upload.
          - Image manipulation module using ImageMagick.
	  - RSS/Atom syndication client module

        * New module: 'dbsql' MySQL datbase support, includes:
          - Prepared statement support (prevents SQL injection attacks).
          - SconeScript integration for MySQL parameter and result types.

        * New module: 'forward' connection forwarding.
        * New module: 'lettuce' (http://www.sconemad.com/lettuce)

0.7.0 2006-06-24 Andrew Wedgbury <wedge@sconemad.com>

	* New configurable pooled multi-threaded design.
	* Non-blocking outgoing connections.
	* Connection forwarding module.
	* Datagram support with virtual channels, making it very easy to write
	datagram servers.
	* TFTP (Trivial File Transfer Protocol) module.

0.6.0 2006-06-21 Andrew Wedgbury <wedge@sconemad.com>
	
	* Implement proper control structures in SconeScript.
	* Make HTTP module more compliant with HTTP/1.1.
	* Add HTTP profiles, can map different ports to different doc trees.
	* External program execution and streaming.
	* Execution of CGI programs from HTTP.
	* Protocol modules for IP, IP6, Bluetooth and Local.
	* Improve docs and add several example modules.
	* Add testbuilder module - an automated test build system with web 
	interface.

